  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "MICHELLE STERN",
    "text": "This ring was given to me in 1992 by the granddaughter of the family that hid my mother during the war. Her name is [INAUDIBLE]. She got it from her grandfather when he passed away. Actually, she got it from her father when he passed away, Bernard Roerink. And Bernard had been given the center part, which is diamonds, as a tie tack for my grandfather, Leo Stofkooper, in approximately 1945. And when I asked my grandmother how it happened that my grandfather had a diamond tie tack, she said that originally it had been a diamond ring that he had given to her and she had made for him into a tie tack. So, it went full circle back to a ring again.",
